A little before this, Peter, the first Norinan Bishop of Lichfield, following the same policy as Remi- gius at Dorchester and John of Tours at Wells, removed the seat of his bishoprick from little Lichfield to greater Chester. He fixed his throne in the minster of St. John without the walls. . . . The stately Norman work which still remains in the church is most likely due to this bishop.
